node.text: Some of your favorite @TikTok creators are coming to @AirbnbExperiences. Go behind the scenes and learn their secrets of self-expression—right from home. Work out with @trevorbell, take better photos with @bonnierzm, make home videos with @itsthemcfarlands, dance with choreographer @arbengiga and more. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Miami baker and @airbnbexperiences host, @laromibakery. Originally from Argentina, she’ll show you how to make traditional alfajores that are sure to sweeten up Mom’s day. For as beautiful as these dulce de leche sandwich cookies turn out, they’re surprisingly simple to make. Follow Romina’s foolproof recipe or join her Online Experience to make a sweet suite of Latin desserts. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Nashville-based singer-songwriter and @airbnbexperiences host, @annebucklemusic. Follow Anne’s simple tricks for crafting a tune, or join her Online Experience for live instruction and melody-making. Link in bio.

node.text:
In March, @AirbnbExperiences hosts all over the world had to stop doing what they love—sharing their interests and passions with others. 
Over the past few weeks, they’ve offered ideas for how to continue hosting even while we’re apart. 
They’ve adapted recipes based on what’s in their pantries, turned living rooms into yoga studios, and choreographed dances for families at home.

Today we’re excited to announce that Airbnb Experiences are now online. You can take a flamenco class with Lidón in Madrid, participate in a tarot card reading with Mak in Austin, or visit a colony of penguins in Cape Town—all from home.

True to Airbnb Experiences in real life, Online Experiences are hosted by remarkable people and set in small groups. Alongside making a new dish, maybe you’ll make a new friend, too.

Thank you to our incredible hosts around the world. We’ll see you online soon —> link in bio.

node.title: Meet Homage Hospitality, the hosts who built the hotel they always wanted.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on July 31, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
With a clay court, two swimming pools, and even pétanque, Superhost Catherine’s majestic villa has everything you need to stage your own personal championship match. If those events don’t go your way, consider adding bazaar navigation—the city is only 15 minutes away. 

Link in bio for world-class fun.

Photo by Airbnb on July 31, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and pool.
Photo by Airbnb on July 31, 2021. May be an image of furniture.
Photo by Airbnb on July 31, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

Photo by Airbnb on July 31, 2021. May be an image of living room.
Photo by Airbnb in Shimogyō-ku, Kyoto. May be an image of bedroom.

node.text:
Superhost Irene’s updated machiya is the kind of home where everything, down to the teacups, seems thoughtfully considered. Though it’s just about as quiet as it looks, it’s also close to the heart of town—and a quick subway ride away from the otherworldly Arashiyama Bamboo Grove.

Link in bio to wishlist.

Photo: @maanahomes

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Kyoto, Japan. May be an image of outdoors and tree.

node.text:
It might look serene, but guests warn that your morning tea might be joined by a staring deer. Jinn, a Superhost and (no surprise) photographer, has composed a garden retreat as comfortable as it is elegant. He also takes his ramen seriously, and will gladly guide you to his favorite spots. 

Link in bio to wishlist.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Tokyo, Japan. May be an image of one or more people and indoor.

node.text:
In an @AirbnbExperience from her Tokyo kitchen, Yumi will show you how to make onigiri (rice balls), atsuyaki-tamago (sweet rolled omelets), and other comfort food. Once you’ve learned her simple but precise techniques, you’ll have a lifelong superpower for picnics, potlucks, or just treating yourself. 

Link in bio for medal-worthy snacks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Valladolid, Yucatan. May be an image of tree and outdoors.

node.text:
When your house is just across the street from one of the world’s most spectacular places to swim (Cenote Suytún), your pool better be something special. Superhost Anette made hers irresistible, a trait it shares with the rest of her modern jungle cottage. Note that the cenote, while indeed unforgettable, has zero hammocks. 

Link in bio to make a splash in the Yucatán.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Panajachel, Solola. May be an image of tree, nature, mountain and lake.

node.text:
The tough part about playing badminton alongside Lake Atitlán is keeping your eyes on the shuttlecock and not the view. Fortunately, Superhost David’s spacious house gives you plenty of ways to soak up its beauty before you play, including stone steps straight down to the water. 

Link in bio for smashing volcanic vistas.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on July 25, 2021. May be an image of nature, body of water, beach and palm trees.

node.text:
From Iceland to the Philippines, an ocean of homes and experiences put you next to—and into—the sea. Whether you surf, snorkel, or just swoon, you’ll come away recharged (and maybe a little salty, in the best way). 

Link in bio to dive in to wishlist-worthy stays for ocean explorers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on July 25, 2021. May be an image of nature, body of water, beach and palm trees.
Photo by Airbnb on July 25, 2021. May be an image of ocean.
Photo by Airbnb on July 25, 2021. May be an image of body of water and nature.
Photo by Airbnb on July 25, 2021. May be an image of nature.
Photo by Airbnb in Shimoda, Shizuoka. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Sunlight through shoji paper and a hundred other traditional touches make this big house a feast for the eyes, but you might remember other sensations even longer, like the smell of sea breezes on cedar. After a day at one of the beaches within walking distance, come home for a long soak in your ofuro (deep bathtub). 

Link in bio to wishlist.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Austin, Texas. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Superhost Adam’s Texas-sized 1971 trailer is your own oasis of calm in the heart of the action. Walk a few blocks for a show at the historic but most definitely still kickin’ Continental Club, or some Tex-Mex from Güero’s. (If you’re hungry from walking around all day or swimming at Barton Springs, order El Presidente.)

Link in bio for a modern classic.

Photo: @airstreamsetc

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on July 22, 2021. May be an image of tree and nature.

node.text:
The private woods surrounding this treehouse might become your favorite place to get lost. After a day of wandering the trails or swimming in the spring water ponds—yep, plural—kick back by the fire, indoors or out. It’s all just an hour from downtown Toronto. 

Link in bio for Superhost Olivier’s forest retreat.

Photos/videos: @underflowr

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Playa Hermosa, Costa Rica. May be an image of tree and pool.

node.text:
If monkeys regularly visit your backyard but guests rave more about how welcome you made them feel, you might be a Superhost. Matthew’s lush villa puts you a few minutes away from black sand beaches and world-class surfing, and he’ll happily help you plan other adventures, like jungle hikes or an Isla Tortuga day trip. 

Link in bio for waves and wildlife.

Photo: @thejunglepalace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Yucca Valley, California. May be an image of living room.

node.text:
Superhosts Bianca and Clint’s 1959 ranch house adds a splash of midcentury color to the stark beauty of the high desert. It’s also just a few miles from the entrance to Joshua Tree National Park. Earn an extra-long soak in the hot tub by hiking the spectacular, aptly named Panorama Loop.

Link in bio for needle-sharp design.

Photo: @JtreeBnB
